Package ohos.event.commonevent

Class CommonEventSubscriber

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.commonevent.CommonEventSubscriber

  • public abstract class CommonEventSubscriber
extends Object
    Provides methods that will be called back when a subscriber receives a new common event.

    CommonEventSubscriber is an abstract class. If you want your application to receive common events from other applications, you must first inherit this class and implement the onReceiveEvent(ohos.event.commonevent.CommonEventData) method. Then, you can use methods provided in CommonEventManager to subscribe to or unsubscribe from certain common events. The received common events will be stored in CommonEventData.

    Since:
    1
    See Also:
    CommonEventManager.subscribeCommonEvent(CommonEventSubscriber), CommonEventManager.unsubscribeCommonEvent(CommonEventSubscriber)
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Notification#CES

      • goAsyncCommonEvent

        public final AsyncCommonEventResult goAsyncCommonEvent​()
        Enables asynchronous processing for the current ordered common event.

        This method is called using the onReceiveEvent(ohos.event.commonevent.CommonEventData) callback method. The common event remains active after being returned from onReceiveEvent(ohos.event.commonevent.CommonEventData). That is, the common event can continue to perform its time-consuming operations on another thread instead of the main thread. However, this does not mean that time-consuming operations can be executed by calling the callback method. In addition, your application is required to call AsyncCommonEventResult#finishCommonEvent() to finish processing the ordered common event before it is complete.

        Returns:
        Returns the asynchronous result of the current ordered common event.
        Since:
        2

      • setCode

        public final void setCode​(int code)
        Sets the result code of the current ordered common event.

        This method takes effect only for ordered common events. You can call CommonEventPublishInfo#setOrdered(boolean) with the input parameter set to true to set a common event ordered. The next subscriber will receive the result code after the code is set.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the custom result code to set. You can set it to any int value.

      • abortCommonEvent

        public final void abortCommonEvent​()
        Aborts the current ordered common event.

        This method takes effect only for ordered common events. Once this method is called, no subscribers will receive this common event. You can call clearAbortCommonEvent() to revoke this operation.

        Since:
        2

      • toString

        public String toString​()
        Description copied from class: Object
        Returns a string representation of the object. In general, the toString method returns a string that "textually represents" this object. The result should be a concise but informative representation that is easy for a person to read. It is recommended that all subclasses override this method.

        The toString method for class Object returns a string consisting of the name of the class of which the object is an instance, the at-sign character `@', and the unsigned hexadecimal representation of the hash code of the object. In other words, this method returns a string equal to the value of: 

         getClass().getName() + '@' + Integer.toHexString(hashCode())
